New Records: Travis Head scored his highest ODI score of 154 not out.
Key Match Events: Travis Head's unbeaten 154 led Australia to a seven-wicket victory.
Marnus Labuschagne contributed 77 not out in an unbroken 148-run stand with Head.
Ben Duckett top-scored for England with 95 off 91 deliveries.
England collapsed from 213 for two to 315 all out.
Adam Zampa took three wickets for 49 runs on his 100th ODI.
Marnus Labuschagne, a part-time bowler, took three wickets.
Travis Head was dropped on six but went on to score 154 not out.
Post-Match Reflections: Harry Brook mentioned that England did everything they planned but it wasn't their day.
Brook also reflected on the decision to bat first and the challenges faced during the middle period.
Ricky Ponting praised the comprehensive run-chase and Travis Head's performance.
Stuart Broad called Travis Head an incredible player and highlighted his strengths.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Australia completed the chase with six overs to spare.
Australia's win marked their 13th successive ODI victory and sixth in a row over England.
